<p>I am trying to use jersey's <a href="https://jersey.java.net/documentation/latest/bean-validation.html" rel="nofollow">bean validation extension</a> to wok. Unfortunately I am not successful so far. I have a class which can be validated:</p>  <pre><code>import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull; import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlElement; import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;  @XmlRootElement class Entity {    @XmlElement   @NotNull   private Double value;  } </code></pre>  <p>I have written a unit test which uses a validator like this:</p>  <pre><code>ValidatorFactory factory = Validation.buildDefaultValidatorFactory(); validator = factory.getValidator(); </code></pre>  <p>In this case everything works as expected, null-valued Entities have a non-empty <code>Set</code> of <code>ConstraintViolation&lt;Entity&gt;</code></p>  <p>Now I added a resource class like this:</p>  <pre><code>@Path("/") @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON + ";charset=utf-8") @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON) public class EntityHandler {    public Response addRequest(@Valid Entity entity) {     // ...   }  } </code></pre>  <p>However, I keep getting null-valued Entities anyways. I would imagine that the method should not be called at all if the Entity fails the test?! I also added this property to my <code>ResourceConfig</code></p>  <pre><code>property(ServerProperties.BV_SEND_ERROR_IN_RESPONSE, true); </code></pre>  <p>I also looked at the corresponding <a href="https://github.com/jersey/jersey/tree/master/examples/bean-validation-webapp" rel="nofollow">example</a>, to no avail. I am using version 2.17 of jersey (and the validation extension). I am a little lost, any ideas?</p>